@sagarafr At present, the behavior of `az resource list --tag ""` is to search all the resources. 
Because when `--tag` is passed in as `""`, it will be changed into an `{}` by method `validate_tag`  [codel link](https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/blob/dev/src/azure-cli-core/azure/cli/core/commands/validators.py#L50
) in `azure-cli-core`.  Then the filter condition of tag will not be added to the rest request, so it will not search for resources by tag.

I personally think the behavior of `--tags ""` in `az vm --delete --tags "" --yes` needs to be consistent with `--tag ""` in `az resource list --tag ""`.

