What about something like this:
```ts
      if (!isEmpty) {
        toSendData[field.name] = value;
      } else if (field.optional) {
        toSendData[field.name] = null;
      }
```

So we would send `null` (`None`), for every empty optional field...
This would be a major breaking change, as both voluptuous serialize and every config flow with optional fields will need to be updated to allow `None`
Or we would add support for it in voluptuous serialize, and depending on that we send `None` for empty optional fields... So a config flow could opt-in to this behavior
